  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 88074e2e0d4f0b8478a99308a4b0d6a4, type: 3}
  m_Name: LostForestTrap
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: GameScripts::BlueMCQCard
  cardName: The Lost Forest Trap
  image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 81a8575930cc7ff4893e54076617bce1, type: 3}
  statement: 
  question: "Forests act as \u201Ccarbon sinks,\u201D soaking up CO2. When a forest
    is cut down or burned for farmland, what happens to all that stored carbon?"
  answers:
  - answer: It disappears.
    messageWhenChosen: Oops! Any time we burn something living, like a plant, or
      something that was once alive, like fossil fuels, it releases CO2 into the
      air. This CO2 will stay in the air forever, unless more trees are planted to
      soak it up!
    correctAnswer: 0
  - answer: Birds eat it all.
    messageWhenChosen: Oops! Any time we burn something living, like a plant, or
      something that was once alive, like fossil fuels, it releases CO2 into the
      air. This CO2 will stay in the air forever, unless more trees are planted to
      soak it up!
    correctAnswer: 0
  - answer: It fills the air.
    messageWhenChosen: 'Correct! Any time we burn something living, like a plant,
      or something that was once alive, like fossil fuels, it releases CO2 into the
      air. This CO2 will stay in the air forever, unless more trees are planted to
      soak it up! '
    correctAnswer: 1
